00:33:22.000 --> 00:33:28.000
 When a character string appears like this in a program, access to it is through a character pointer.

00:33:28.000 --> 00:33:32.000
 What printf receives is a pointer to the character array.

00:33:32.000 --> 00:33:37.000
 Character arrays, of course, need not be function arguments.

00:33:37.000 --> 00:33:50.000
